Scipio proceeds to the island of Ebusus, and, after ineffectually besieging its chief town for two days, pillages the adjacent district, and burns several villages. Ambassa- dors from the Balearic islands sue for peace. Many of the Spanish peoples give hostages to Scipio. Scipio landing his troops marches towards the Forest of Castulo. Hasdrubal withdraws into Lusitania. —B.c. 217.
